{
  "stem": "2723.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because when I came to again, I was sufficiently well to sit in the sun.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember sitting with my back to the barracks and then suddenly realizing I had adapted to that lot.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How on Earth will I adapt to what was ahead?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until the day when we were told that because of these Czech girls that were in the camp-- those who were of Czechoslovakian nationality are to be taken away, uh, first, back to their country, by means not yet known to us.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had very little friendship shown to us, um, by the Czech girls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, they were very matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They did what was expected of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But warmth, or what I was hoping for, was never forthcoming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one day, they notified us that the trucks are on the way.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think it must have been somewhere at the very end of, uh, May that, indeed, we set off on chauffeur-driven-- sorry, Czech-chauffeured trucks.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Later on, I was told they were, in fact, camp inmates who had already been back and come to get us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I couldn't understand how they could have done it because the places were so totally, um, bombed, and the roads were nonexistent.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They found a way of zig-zagging their way across.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember the trip back with bad memories, very bad memories, because the hostility of some of the Czechs was visible, painful.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I came across the Norwegian doctor who helped my ear and his Czech assistant doctor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Czech assistant doctor who fed me and brought me, um, the food and encouragement was one of those who turned away when I came back free and made it very obvious to me that he had very little time for Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
